<title>UK: Hambros arm set to back hotel buyout - report.</title>
<headline>Hambros arm set to back hotel buyout - report.</headline>
<dateline>LONDON 1997-01-16</dateline>
<text>
<p>Hambros Plc venture capital arm Hambro European Ventures is preparing to back a buyout of 90 million stg ($151 million) or more of 25 hotels put up for sale by Queens Moat Houses, the Guardian said on Thursday.</p>
<p>&quot;The Hambro bid is understood to have prevailed over a similar offer from Adams Hotels, a small Glasgow-based company which had secured funding from the Royal Bank of Scotland,&quot; the Guardian report said.</p>
<p>The newspaper said the deal is expected to be tied up next month.</p>
